<h2 id="faqs"><a href="#faqs">Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs)</a></h2>

<h3 id="general"><a href="#general">General</a></h3>
<ul>
  <li>
    <strong>Is this event really free?</strong>
    <p>YES — The organisers are committed to creating a community and receive no benefit from the event other than the community. We rely on the support of the venue hosts for a free event space.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Where are events held?</strong>
    <p>Events are held in and around Bournemouth, UK. Location details are on each event page. See our <a href="/venues.html">Venues page</a> for more about the spaces we use.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>How often do events run?</strong>
    <p>We aim to run an event every month, usually on the last Wednesday of the month. See <a href="/#upcoming-events">Upcoming Events</a> on our home page for the next date.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Is there a code of conduct?</strong>
    <p>YES, and it will be strictly followed: <a href="/code-of-conduct.html">Code of Conduct</a></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>How do we get in touch?</strong>
    <p>All ways to get in touch are on our website: <a href="/contact-us.html">devdottalk.uk</a></p>
  </li>
</ul>

<h3 id="attending-faqs"><a href="#attending-faqs">Attending</a></h3>
<ul>
  <li>
    <strong>What can I expect at a {dev.talk} event?</strong>
    <p>A typical event runs for around 2 hours. After check-in you'll receive a name badge and can grab a soft drink while networking. The evening features two software-focused talks, each followed by audience Q&amp;A, with a networking break in between. There's often time to chat after the event too. See our <a href="/attending.html">Attending page</a> for the full typical agenda.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Do I need to register / get a ticket?</strong>
    <p>Yes — free tickets are required to help us manage capacity. <a href="/tickets">Tickets are available here</a>. If your plans change, please cancel so others can take your spot.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>I am just learning, can I come?</strong>
    <p>YES — Everyone is welcome. Come and meet people from all stages in their career.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Can I bring a friend or colleague?</strong>
    <p>Absolutely! Everyone is welcome — they just need to grab their own free <a href="/tickets">ticket</a>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Will there be refreshments?</strong>
    <p>Soft drinks and biscuits will be provided.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>What if I can't make it after registering?</strong>
    <p>Please cancel your <a href="/tickets">ticket</a> via the ticketing app or email us at <a href="mailto:contactus@devdottalk.uk">contactus@devdottalk.uk</a>. This helps us manage capacity and allows others to attend.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Is the venue accessible?</strong>
    <p>We aim to choose accessible venues for all our events. Specific accessibility information — including step-free access, lifts, and parking — is included on each event page.</p>
  </li>
</ul>

<h3 id="speaking-faqs"><a href="#speaking-faqs">Speaking</a></h3>
<ul>
  <li>
    <strong>How do I become a speaker?</strong>
    <p>We welcome speakers of all experience levels — from lightning talks to in-depth sessions! Visit our <a href="/call-for-speakers.html">Call for Speakers</a> page to find out more and submit your proposal. We'll help you with ideas, structure, and practice if needed.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Will my talk be recorded?</strong>
    <p>Yes — talks are usually recorded and uploaded to our <a href="/youtube" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">YouTube channel</a>. If you have any concerns about recording, please let the organisers know in advance.</p>
  </li>
</ul>

<h3 id="community-faqs"><a href="#community-faqs">Community &amp; Support</a></h3>
<ul>
  <li>
    <strong>Are there going to be recruitment agencies attending?</strong>
    <p>No selling or promotion of services is allowed at our event. Any person found doing so will be asked to leave.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Can we contribute to the refreshments?</strong>
    <p>Sure — refreshments are currently provided by the organisers (we have no sponsors). If you'd like to help out, check out our <a href="/support-us" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Support Us link</a>.</p>
  </li>
</ul>
